06:21.460 --> 06:29.580
This is Bill Vernon. And Daryl Lane. One of the most popular and unique fantasy
authors ever was J.R.R. Tolkien, whose trilogy about hobbits, The Lord of the

06:29.580 --> 06:37.300
Rings, came out of the 1950s. Tolkien has become a phenomenon. His books have
gone through countless printings. There are Tolkien societies and clubs all over

06:37.300 --> 06:44.300
the world. And his Middle Earth has, for many readers, become a place as real as
our own world. There have been four or five Tolkien organizations in this

06:44.300 --> 06:51.800
country, and others scattered all over the world. But most successful is the
British Tolkien Society. The Science Fiction Radio Show spoke with Lester

06:51.800 --> 06:59.160
Simons, the membership secretary of the Tolkien Society, when he came to this
country for a Tolkien moot at the World Science Fiction Convention in Denver. We

06:59.160 --> 07:12.800
asked him to tell us about the Tolkien Society. The Society was founded in
England in 1969 with a very small group of members. The Society has grown

07:12.800 --> 07:28.940
gradually over the years. Various notices in various books, directory listings
and so on. We now have 1,200 members, approximately, in 26 countries throughout

07:28.940 --> 07:39.520
the world. So although we're based in England, I think we have the largest
worldwide spread. One way members of the Tolkien Society correspond among

07:39.520 --> 07:51.060
themselves is through the Society's publications. We have two regular
publications. Amon Hen is approximately bi-monthly. It's a bulletin and a

07:51.060 --> 08:08.340
newsletter, letters of comment from members, short articles, short poems, small
artwork. It's really for immediate consumption, the ephemeral material. And the

08:08.340 --> 08:19.420
other publication is Mallorn, the journal, very much more academic. It comes
out, we hope, twice a year. So sometimes we get a Mallorn and an Amon Hen

08:19.420 --> 08:33.740
together. Mallorn is a larger format. It has longer poems. Sometimes they run to
three pages. Members' own poems. In the Tolkien manner, some of them are

08:33.740 --> 08:50.900
imitations of Tolkien's style. Others are members' own work in their own styles.
Essays, longer book reviews, articles of rather more specific interest. And it

08:50.900 --> 09:01.880
is very much less time-dependent. We asked Simons if there were activities in
fellowship among members. Oh, yes, considerable. Our local groups are called

09:01.880 --> 09:14.720
Smiles, from the Hobbit. A smile is a comfortable Hobbit hole. And we hope that
our members feel as comfortable in our smiles as they would in a Hobbit home. We

09:14.720 --> 09:24.900
have smiles in many countries. In some countries, there just aren't enough
members to get together because they're too widely separated. But in England,

09:24.920 --> 09:39.040
there are smiles all over the country. They run themselves as they wish. Some of
them are very formal. Some have costume. Others don't. Some publish their own

09:39.040 --> 09:52.820
little newsletters with subsequent meeting venues, short reviews, little
artwork. It just depends on what the members in any particular area wish to do.

09:53.620 --> 10:01.000
There are also two national meetings annually for the society. One is a formal
business meeting. The other is the Oxenmoot, held on a weekend in late

10:01.000 --> 10:11.740
September. And it is a weekend where members who otherwise don't normally see
other people come together. Smiles send representative groups. Other societies

10:11.740 --> 10:23.600
send representative groups. This year we should have groups from Stockholm.
There will be a representative from America. There will be groups from all over

10:23.600 --> 10:34.060
the United Kingdom. And it is just a weekend of being in company of Tolkien
people. More about the Tolkien Society on our next show.

