14:12.060 --> 14:30.440
may be other tales filling in some gaps in Middle-earth. But all we know is that
the papers sat in box files on a table eight feet long. There is a considerable

14:30.440 --> 14:42.200
amount of material. How much of it is publishable is not known. How much of it
is readable is, again, a matter of debate, because towards the end of his life,

14:42.280 --> 14:51.740
the professor's handwriting became not so much untidy as illegible, and even
Christopher can't read it. Finally, we wondered if there was enough material to

14:51.740 --> 15:02.160
keep the Tolkien Society in existence. Wouldn't it run out of things to do after
a while? Well, there are always new people coming in to the societies. People

15:02.160 --> 15:11.860
